# Online Shopping Delivery System – Composite Design Pattern

## Project Overview
This project demonstrates the Composite Design Pattern in Java using an online shopping delivery system.

It focuses on representing hierarchical structures in a simple and scalable way and calculating total order price.

---

## Design Pattern Used
### Composite Design Pattern (Structural Pattern)

---

## Case Study: Delivery System Structure

The system consists of:

- Products (Leaf nodes)
- Boxes (Composite nodes)

### Box Structure
A box can contain:
- Products
- Smaller boxes
- Nested boxes (multi-level structure)

---

## Main Objective
Calculate the total price of all products inside the main box, regardless of nesting depth.

---

## Why Composite Pattern?

- Treats products and boxes the same way
- Simplifies recursive calculations
- Removes complex conditional logic
- Improves scalability

---

## System Benefits

- Handles nested structures easily
- Clean and reusable design
- Uniform component handling
- Simple price calculation

---

## Technologies Used

- Java
- OOP Principles
- Composite Design Pattern

---

## Summary
This project shows how Composite Pattern simplifies hierarchical systems by treating individual objects and groups uniformly.
